text:
Content & Prompt Templates Reusable patterns for building certificate content Canvas content page scaffold (recommended) H2: Page Title Intro paragraph (1 short paragraph): what learners will gain H3: Why This Matters (2–3 bullets) H3: Key Concepts (2–4 short explanations) H3: Activity or Knowledge Check (short, actionable) H3: Optional: Discipline-specific variants (faculty/staff/student) Embed section (if needed): responsive iframe wrapper + instructions Prompt template: “Design-first page drafting” Use this when drafting a Canvas page while preserving human authority. Prompt: You are helping draft a Canvas content page for the Generative AI Fluency Certificate.
Follow this structure exactly: H2 title; intro paragraph; H3 Why This Matters (bullets); H3 Key Concepts; H3 Activity/Knowledge Check.
Constraints: Keep it tool-agnostic unless the page explicitly teaches a tool. Use UIUC-friendly tone: clear, direct, non-hype. Include at least one “boundary” sentence describing what the concept is NOT.
Topic: {paste topic}
Audience: {faculty/staff/students/varied}
Length: ~350–600 words Prompt template: “Document a design decision” (internal) Prompt: Summarize the following design discussion into a decision log entry.
Output: Decision (1 sentence) Rationale (2–4 bullets) Tradeoffs (1–3 bullets) Follow-ups (bullets, if any)
Text to summarize: {paste thread or notes}
